AmazonS3 --> Web service for hosting static websites
Amazon route 53 --> Maps domain names to ip address (dns helper)
Cloudfront --> Cache geographically near customer so that shit's faster

Amazon EC2 ---> it's a computer in the cloud using VMS.
AMAZON MACHINE IMAGE -- AMI -> hosts it for me so i dont have to do LAMP configuration

EC2 Instance + WordPress AMI = WP on AWS Cloud in 2 Minutes!

**************************************************************************
setting my own website

1. Create the amazon bucket for my website. 

vicepresidentemusic.com --> root domain bucket
logs.vicepresidentemusic.com --> log bucket ---> this contains metadata 
www.vicepresidentemusic.com --> subdomain bucket ---> redirects to root domain bucket

registering a custom domain name --> changing from http://example.com.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com/ to vicepresidentemusic.com.

2. configure the custom domain name

Go on the console and create the bucket to the namespace. 

** enable logging to get analytics and stuff

a. set permissions --> click on root domain -> permissions -> set the text template
b. set logins -> click on root domain -> logins -> enable -> target bucket is logs.etc -> target prefix is root/

3. deploy website -- follow tutorial

etc . . . go here: http://docs.aws.amazon.com/gettingstarted/latest/swh/website-hosting-intro.html

